SOURCELONG:Unearthed Arcana - Horror Subclasses	SOURCESHORT:UA	SOURCEWEB:https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/dnd/ua	SOURCEDATE:2025-01

###Block Artificer Subclass																																
Reanimator	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Artificer Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Reanimators defy the laws of nature in pursuit of gruesome experiment. These grim Artificers stitch together servants from disparate corpses, use foul magic to strengthen the living, and transform the art of necromancy into a terrifying science.	KEY:Artificer Subclass ~ Reanimator																		ABILITY:Artificer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Reanimator ~ Reanimator Spells|PREVAREQ:ArtificerLVL,3	ABILITY:Artificer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Reanimator ~ Jolt to Life|PREVAREQ:ArtificerLVL,3	ABILITY:Artificer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Reanimator ~ Reanimated Companion|PREVAREQ:ArtificerLVL,3	ABILITY:Artificer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Reanimator ~ Strange Modification|PREVAREQ:ArtificerLVL,5	ABILITY:Artificer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Reanimator ~ Improved Reanimation|PREVAREQ:ArtificerLVL,9	ABILITY:Artificer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Reanimator ~ Prometheian Reanimation|PREVAREQ:ArtificerLVL,15				SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01e5	SOURCEPAGE:UA

Reanimator Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Reanimator.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach an Artificer level specified in the Reanimator Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Reanimator ~ Reanimator Spells														SPELLS:Reanimator Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ArtificerLVL|False Life|Spare the Dying|Witch Bolt|PREVARGTEQ:ArtificerLVL,3	SPELLS:Reanimator Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ArtificerLVL|Blindness/Deafness|Enhance Ability|PREVARGTEQ:ArtificerLVL,5	SPELLS:Reanimator Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ArtificerLVL|Animate Dead|Lightning Bolt|PREVARGTEQ:ArtificerLVL,9	SPELLS:Reanimator Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ArtificerLVL|Blight|Death Ward|PREVARGTEQ:ArtificerLVL,13	SPELLS:Reanimator Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ArtificerLVL|Antilife Shell|Raise Dead|PREVARGTEQ:ArtificerLVL,17								SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01e5a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Jolt of Life	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Reanimator.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast Spare the Dying, you can modify the spell so that it sends a jolt of electricity through the target, reviving it. The target regains 1 Hit Point, and each creature in a 10-foot Emanation originating from the target makes a Dexterity saving throw against your spell save DC, taking Lightning damage equal to 1d4 plus half your Artificer level (round up) on a failed save or half as much damage on a successful one. You can modify the spell this way a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Reanimator ~ Jolt of Life																										SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01e5b	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Reanimated Companion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Reanimator.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Using Tinker’s Tools or another type of Artisan’s Tools with which you have proficiency, you can take a Magic action to create a Reanimated Companion (see the stat block) through the power of necromancy and science. The companion manifests in an unoccupied space within 5 feet of you. You determine the companion’s appearance; your choices don’t affect the companion’s game statistics.The companion is Friendly to you and your allies and obeys you. It lasts until you finish a Long Rest or until you take a Magic action to dismiss it early, at which point it harmlessly collapses into a pile of viscera. It immediately drops to 0 Hit Points and dies (triggering its Death Burst trait) if you die. Once you create a companion, you can’t do so again until you finish a Long Rest or expend a spell slot to create one. You can have only one companion at a time and can’t create one while your companion is present.	KEY:Reanimator ~ Reanimated Companion						BONUS:VAR|ReanimatedCompanionLVL|ArtificerLVL								ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Reanimated Companion												SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01e5c	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Strange Modifications	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Reanimator.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you create a Reanimated Companion, it gains one of the following options of your choice; choose when you create the companion. &nl; Arcane Conduit. You can cast spells as though you were in the companion’s space, but you must use your own senses. Once per turn, when you cast an Artificer spell from the Evocation or Necromancy schools and deal damage while your companion is within 120 feet of you, you can add your Intelligence modifier to one damage roll of that spell. &nl; Ferocity. When you command your companion to take the Dreadful Swipe action, the companion can use it twice.	KEY:Reanimator ~ Strange Modification		DEFINE:StrangeModificationLVL|0				BONUS:VAR|StrangeModificationLVL|1																				SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01e5a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Improved Reanimation	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Reanimator.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You experiment and alter your companion further. Whenever you create a Reanimated Companion, it gains one of the following options of your choice; choose when you create the companion.	KEY:Reanimator ~ Improved Reanimation		DEFINE:ImprovedModificationLVL|0				BONUS:VAR|ImprovedModificationLVL|1																				SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01e5a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Prometheian Reanimation	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Reanimator.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have mastered the science of revivification, granting you the following benefits. &nl; Facilitated Revival. When you cast Revivify or Raise Dead, the cost of any Material components needed for that spell is halved. &nl; Improved Companion. The damage of your Reanimated Companion’s Death Burst increases to 4d6. Necrotic damage dealt by your companion ignores Resistance. &nl; Life Transfer. You can siphon the animating magic of your companion to bolster yourself. When you take damage, you can take a Reaction to cause your Reanimated Companion to drop to 0 Hit Points. The companion immediately dies (triggering its Death Burst trait), and you regain a number of Hit Points equal to your Artificer level.	KEY:Reanimator ~ Prometheian Reanimation		DEFINE:PrometheianReanimationLVL|0				BONUS:VAR|PrometheianReanimationLVL|1																				SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01e5a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Bladesong	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Artificer Class Feature.Class Feature.Reanimator.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:.	KEY:Reanimator ~ Bladesong																										SORTKEY:Class_Artificer_01e5a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
